21. The Investment Policy shall, at the minimum, include:
(1) The investment criteria and objectives to be achieved while undertaking
investment transactions, keeping in view the various regulatory / statutory
guidelines and a UCB's own internal requirements;
(2) Securities in which investments may be made;
(3) Derivatives in which a UCB having Authorised Dealer's licence, wherever
allowed, can transact;
(4) The authority to put through deals;
(5) Procedure for obtaining the sanction of the appropriate authority and
putting through deals;
(6) Adherence to various prudential exposure limits including quantity
(ceiling) and quality of each type of security to be held on its own
investment account;
(7) Policy regarding internal control mechanism, accounting standards, audit,
review, dealings through brokers, systems for management of various
risks, guidelines for valuation of the portfolio, and the reporting systems;
(8) Nature and extent of investments intended to be made in non-SLR
securities, the risk management systems for capturing and analysing the
risk parameters, stop-loss limits for holding / divesting the investments,
and remedial measures; and
(9) Proper risk management systems for making investment in non-SLR
securities which shall include entry-level minimum credit ratings / quality
standards and industry-wise, maturity-wise, duration-wise, issuer-wise,

86. A UCB fulfilling the following conditions shall have the option to undertake intra-
day short sale in government securities.
(1) NDS-OM membership;
(2) Net-worth of ₹25 crore;
(3) Applicable minimum CRAR;
(4) Net NPA of not more than 3 per cent;
(5) Sound risk management practices;

109. A scheduled UCB, fulfilling the following conditions, shall be eligible to
undertake repo transactions in corporate bonds:
(1) Applicable minimum CRAR plus 1 per cent;
(2) Gross NPA of less than 5 per cent;
(3) Continuous record of profits during the previous three financial years;
(4) Sound risk management practices; and
(5) Concurrent audit of the Investment portfolio (as required in paragraph
140 of these Directions).

127. As per paragraph 120 and 121 above, a UCB fulfilling the following criteria shall
have the option to accept deposits from other UCBs:
(1) Applicable minimum CRAR plus 1 per cent;
(2) Gross Non Performing Assets (NPAs) of less than 7 per cent and Net
NPAs of not more than 3 per cent;
(3) Net profit for at least three out of the preceding four years subject to it not
having incurred a net loss in the immediately preceding year;
(4) No default in the maintenance of CRR / SLR during the preceding
financial year;
(5) Sound internal control system with at least two professional directors on
the Board; and
(6) Core Banking Solution (CBS) fully implemented.

